What is the formula to calculate the average age of a specific customer group who made a purchase in the last [N] days, with a total cost of over [$X], by joining the customer and purchase tables using the customer ID as the key in Java? 
Here's the SQL query to accomplish this:
SELECT AVG(customer.age) FROM customer INNER JOIN purchase ON customer.customer_id = purchase.customer_id WHERE purchase.date >= DATEADD(day, -[N], GETDATE()) AND purchase.total_cost > [$X];
To execute this query in Java, you can use JDBC (Java Database Connectivity) to connect to your database and run the query. Here's an example code snippet:
String url = "jdbc:mysql://localhost/mydatabase";
String user = "username";
String password = "password";
Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, password);
String sql = "SELECT AVG(customer.age) FROM customer INNER JOIN purchase ON customer.customer_id = purchase.customer_id WHERE purchase.date >= DATEADD(day, -[N], GETDATE()) AND purchase.total_cost > [$X];";
Statement statement = connection.createStatement();
ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(sql);
while (resultSet.next()) {
    double averageAge = resultSet.getDouble(1);
    System.out.println("The average age is: " + averageAge);
}
resultSet.close();
statement.close();
connection.close();

