Yes, I can help you with that. Here is a PHP code that uses the Datamuse API to generate synonyms for the word "hungry" and replaces it in the sentence "It's time for supper and I am famished" with each synonym to create new sentences:
```
<?php
// Define the Datamuse API endpoint
$endpoint = 'https://api.datamuse.com/words';
// Define the word to search for synonyms
$word = 'hungry';
// Define the sentence to replace the word in
$sentence = "It's time for supper and I am famished";
// Send a request to the Datamuse API to get synonyms for the word
$response = file_get_contents("$endpoint?rel_syn=$word");
// Decode the JSON response into an array
$synonyms = json_decode($response, true);
// Loop through each synonym and replace the word in the sentence with it
foreach ($synonyms as $synonym) {
    $newSentence = str_replace($word, $synonym['word'], $sentence);
    echo $newSentence . "\n";
}
?>
```
To create a new sentence using only the synonyms in alphabetical order, without repeating any synonym, you can modify the code as follows:
```
<?php
// Define the Datamuse API endpoint
$endpoint = 'https://api.datamuse.com/words';
// Define the word to search for synonyms
$word = 'hungry';
// Send a request to the Datamuse API to get synonyms for the word
$response = file_get_contents("$endpoint?rel_syn=$word");
// Decode the JSON response into an array
$synonyms = json_decode($response, true);
// Sort the synonyms alphabetically
sort($synonyms);
// Remove any duplicates
$synonyms = array_unique($synonyms, SORT_REGULAR);
// Create a new sentence using only the synonyms in alphabetical order, without repeating any synonym
