Certainly! Here's the modified PHP code for the bubble sort algorithm that sorts an array of negative floating-point numbers in descending order:
```
function bubbleSort($arr) {
    $n = count($arr);
    for ($i = 0; $i < $n; $i++) {
        for ($j = 0; $j < $n - $i - 1; $j++) {
            if ($arr[$j] < $arr[$j + 1]) {
                $temp = $arr[$j];
                $arr[$j] = $arr[$j + 1];
                $arr[$j + 1] = $temp;
            }
        }
    }
    // Find the number closest to zero
    $closest_to_zero = $arr[0];
    foreach($arr as $num) {
        if(abs($num) < abs($closest_to_zero)) {
            $closest_to_zero = $num;
        }
    }
    // Move the number closest to zero to the end of the array
    $index = array_search($closest_to_zero, $arr);
    unset($arr[$index]);
    $arr[] = $closest_to_zero;
    // Return the sorted array
    return $arr;
}
```
This code first sorts the array in descending order using the bubble sort algorithm. It then finds the number closest to zero by iterating through the array and comparing the absolute values of each number. Finally, it moves the number closest to zero to the end of the array using `array_search()` and `unset()`.

