You can use the Natural Language Processing (NLP) library in C# called Stanford.NLP to analyze the parts of speech in a sentence. To remove punctuation marks, you can use the regular expressions in C#. Here's a sample code that demonstrates how to analyze the parts of speech and remove punctuation marks in a sentence:
```csharp
using System;
